Saint Paul Minnesota - the most livable city in America

What's Happening

Stamped poem in Saint Paul Sidewalk that reads: I don't know enough / about balance to tell you / how to do it / I think, though, / it's in the trying / and the letting go / that the scales measuring / right and wrong - quiver / and stand still

Submit Your Sidewalk Poem Today

Saint Paul's Sidewalk Poetry Contest is back. Poems submissions are due by April 15 and can be in English, Spanish, Hmong, Somali or Dakota.

 Flooding

Spring Flooding Information

Click here for more information about flooding in Saint Paul, including road closures, park and trail closures, forecast charts, flood prep tips and resources, and a river cam.
Como Pool Lifeguard

Swimming Lessons & Lifeguard Training

Register online for summer swimming lessons, sailing classes, and lifeguard training.

 Spring Egg Hunt

Spring Celebrations & Activities

Hop into springtime with these fun activities and events.
Volunteers with trash at the Citywide Cleanup.

Citywide Spring Cleanup on April 27

Each year, hundreds of volunteers gather across Saint Paul for the Citywide Spring Cleanup to pick up garbage that has recently become exposed due to the melting snow.

 Mayor Melvin Carter at Allianz Field

Scarves Up, Saint Paul!

Start planning your trip to Allianz Field for the inaugural season
